{{Infobox language | name = Bantenese language | nativename = Bahasa Sunda Banten | region = [[Banten]] and [[West Java]], [[Indonesia]] | speakers = 3,350,000 | date = 2015 | ref = <ref>{{cite book|author=Mikael Parkvall|title=Världens 100 största språk 2007|year=|publisher=[[Nationalencyklopedin]]|oclc=}}</ref> | familycolor = Austronesian | fam2 = [[Nuclear Malayo-Polynesian languages|Nuclear Malayo-Polynesian]] | fam3 = [[Malayo-Sumbawan languages|Malayo-Sumbawan]] | fam4 = [[Sundanese language|Sundanese]]-[[Baduy language|Baduy]] | fam5 = [[Sundanese language|Sundanese]] | script = [[Sundanese script]] | iso3 = | isoexception = dialect | glotto = bant1285 | glottorefname = Bantenese }}
'''Bantenese language''', '''Western Sundanese language''' or '''Western Sundanese dialect''' is a dialect of [[Sundanese language]] spoken by the [[Bantenese people|Bantenese]] and [[Sundanese people|Sundanese]] native to Banten and the western side of [[Bogor Regency]]. The western Bogor area comprises the Jasinga Raya region, which covers Jasinga,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://heibogorcom.wordpress.com/2015/09/04/jasinga-bagian-bogor-yang-banten-secara-kultural/ |title=Jasinga, Bagian Bogor yang Banten Secara Kultural |author= |publisher=HEIBOGOR |date=4 September 2015 |accessdate=2017-07-18}}</ref> Cigudeg, Tenjo, Nanggung, Parungpanjang, Sukujaya subdistrict<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kecamatanjasinga.bogorkab.go.id/index.php/multisite/post/3620/asal-usul-nama-jasinga#.WW2TloSGOM9 |title=Asal Usul Nama Jasinga |author=Kalakay Jasinga |publisher=Kecamatan Jasinga Kabupaten Bogor |date=25 April 2016 |accessdate=2017-07-18}}</ref> and also the northwestern parts of [[Sukabumi Regency]]. The Bantenese language is the [[lingua franca]] of the ''Kasepuhan Ciptagelar'' traditional community in Cisolok subdistrict, and the ''Kasepuhan Banten Kidul'' traditional community.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZV0NkADi2dc |title=KASEPUHAN CIPTAGELAR (full movie) |author=Watchdoc Image |publisher=YouTube |date=29 November 2015 |accessdate=2017-07-18}}</ref>
The regional government of Banten is currently making a significant approach to preserve this dialect through a news program entitled ''Beja ti Lembur'', which was aired by the regional CTV Banten network in Bantenese language.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bantenprov.go.id/upload/Konten%20statis/WARISAN%20BUDAYA%20BANTEN.pdf |title=Warisan Budaya Banten |author=Dr. Taufiqurokhman, Hari Widodo, SH. MH., Muhammad Gunawan & Sulaeman Lambe |publisher=Biro Humas & Protokol Setda Provinsi Banten |date=2014 |accessdate=2017-07-18}}</ref>
==Geographic distribution== [[File:Mataram Sultanate in Sultan Agung Reign id.svg|thumb|left|Area of the [[Mataram Sultanate]] kingdom that controls the [[Parahyangan]] region.]] The Bantenese language in general does not recognize [[Register (sociolinguistics)|registers]] of language, due to the fact that [[Banten]] was never under the rule or influence of the [[Mataram Sultanate]],<ref>{{cite book|author=Claude Guillot, Hasan Muarif Ambary & Jacques Dumarçay|title=Banten|year=1990|publisher=Gramedia Book Publishing Division|isbn=97-940-3922-5}}</ref> differed from the Priangan dialect spoken in the [[Parahyangan]] region. This has caused the Bantenese language to be seen as a language that is still closely related to the old [[Sundanese language]].
[[File:Linguistic map West Java.png|thumb|right|Linguistic map of [[West Java]], [[Banten]] and [[Jakarta]].]] Today, the Bantenese language is categorized as a western dialect of [[Sundanese language]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bacatangerang.com/bahasa-sunda-tangerang-aing-tangerang-jasa/|title=Bahasa Sunda Tangerang (Aing Tangerang Jasa) - Baca Tangerang|website=www.bacatangerang.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-10-11}}</ref> This dialect is generally spoken mostly in the southern region of [[Banten]], which are [[Lebak Regency|Lebak]] (including Cilangkahan region), and [[Pandeglang Regency]] (including Caringin and Cibaliung). In the northern [[Serang Regency]], this language is used daily by the people of Ciomas, Pabuaran, Padarincang, [[Cinangka]], Baros, Petir, Cikeusal, Kopo, Cikande, Pamarayan and parts of Anyar subdistrict.<ref name="GDSDKS">{{cite book|author=Agus Suriamiharja, Hidayat & Yoyo Mulyana|title=Geografi dialek Sunda di Kabupaten Serang|year=1981|publisher=Pusat Pembinaan dan Pengembangan Bahasa, Departemen Pendidikan dan Kebudayaa|oclc=64958736}}</ref> This dialect is also used by Sundanese transmigrants in [[Central Lampung Regency]], [[Lampung]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://anjunganlampung.com/regency-city/kabupaten-lampung-tengah/|title=Kabupaten Lampung Tengah {{!}} Anjungan Lampung|website=anjunganlampung.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2017-10-24}}</ref>
In [[Serang Regency]], Bantenese language and Bantenese Javanese are both used daily by the people of Anyar, Mancak, Waringinkurung, Taktakan, Cipocok Jaya, Walantaka, as well as Kragilan subdistrict.<ref name="GDSDKS" /> This dialect is also used in some parts of [[Tangerang Regency]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tangselpos.co.id/2015/10/28/mulok-bahasa-sunda-terancam-punah/ |title=Mulok Bahasa Sunda Terancam Punah |author= |publisher=Tangsel Pos |date=28 August 2015 |accessdate=2017-07-18}}</ref> especially in its southern, southwestern, midwest and northern parts,<ref>{{cite book|author=Taufik Ampera, Cece Subarna & Tien Wartini|title=Bahasa dan sastra daerah di Kabupaten Tangerang : pengkajian budaya dan nilai-nilai tradisional pengkajian budaya dan nilai-nilai tradisional|year=2004|publisher=Pemerintah Kabupaten Tangerang|oclc=}}</ref> as well as in cities of [[Tangerang]] and [[South Tangerang]].<ref>{{cite book|author=Multamia R. M. T. Lauder|title=Pemetaan dan distribusi bahasa-bahasa di Tangerang|year=1993|publisher=Departemen Pendidikan dan Kebudayaan|isbn=97-945-9368-0}}</ref>
The [[Baduy people]] in the Leuwidamar subdistrict of the [[Lebak Regency]] are active speakers of another [[Sundanese language]] dialect known as [[Baduy language|Baduy dialect]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://joshuaproject.net/languages/bac |title=Language: Badui |publisher=[[Joshua Project]] |date= |accessdate=2017-07-18}}</ref>
