{{Infobox language |name=Maojia |states=China |region=[[Hunan]], [[Guangxi]] |ethnicity=[[Miao people|Miao]] |speakers=200,000 |date=1991 |ref=<ref name="Chen2013"/> |familycolor=mixed |family=[[mixed language|mixed]] [[Chinese language|Chinese]]–[[Miao languages|Miao]] |iso3=none |glotto=none }}
'''Maojia''' (猫家 ''{{IPA|mau˥ka˥}}''<ref name="Chen2013">Chen, Qiguang [陈其光] (2013). ''Miao and Yao language'' [苗瑶语文]. Beijing: China Minzu University Press.</ref>) is a [[mixed language]] in Southern China. Some scholars think Maojiahua is a [[Hmongic]] dialect of [[Hmong-Mien languages]], although it absorbs a lot of Chinese words. Others treat Maojiahua as [[Chinese dialect]] which mixes with [[Hmong-Mien languages]].
Maojiahua is spoken by about 200,000 people of Au-Ka (Aoka 奥卡) [[Miao people|Miao]] [[ethnic group|ethnicity]] in [[Chengbu Miao Autonomous County|Chengbu]], [[Suining County, Hunan|Suining]], [[Wugang, Hunan|Wugang]] and [[Suining County, Hunan|Suining]] in southwest part of [[Hunan Province]], as well as in [[Ziyuan County|Ziyuan]] and [[Longsheng County|Longsheng]] in north part of Guangxi Province.<ref>http://asiaharvest.org/wp-content/themes/asia/docs/people-groups/China/chinaPeoples/A/Aoka.pdf</ref>
According to Chen Qiguang (2013:32),<ref name="Chen2013"/> "Maojia" (''{{IPA|mau˥ka˥}}''), also known as "Qingyi Miao 青衣苗", is spoken mostly in [[Chengbu Miao Autonomous County|Chengbu County]], [[Hunan]], and also in Suining, Wugang, Longsheng, and Ziyuan counties. There is a total of about 120,000 speakers. The representative dialect given in Chen (2013) is that of Xintang Village 信塘村, Yangshi Township 羊石乡, [[Chengbu Miao Autonomous County]], Hunan Province. Li (2004) covers various dialects of Qingyi Miao in detail.
