{{Infobox musical artist | name = The Outside Track | image = | image_size = | landscape = | alt = | caption = | background = group_or_band | alias = | origin = [[Limerick, Ireland|Limerick]], Ireland | genre = [[Celtic Music|Pan Celtic]] | years_active = {{start date|2005}}-present | label = | associated_acts = | website = http://www.theoutsidetrack.com | current_members = {{unbulleted list|Mairi Rankin, Teresa Horgan, Fiona Black, Ailie Robertson, Michael Ferrie}} | past_members = {{unbulleted list|Aoife Scott}}<ref>{{cite web|author=Andrea Smith |url=http://www.independent.ie/life/family/family-features/bondings-black-is-the-colour-how-singer-aoife-scott-knew-andy-meaney-was-the-guy-for-her-34429048.html |title=Bondings: Black is the colour - how singer Aoife Scott knew Andy Meaney was the guy for her |website=Independent.ie |date= |accessdate=2016-02-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Rannie Gillis|url=http://www.capebretonpost.com/Opinion/Columnists/2015-10-16/article-4310838/Two-for-the-price-of-one-in-Boisdale/1 |title=Two for the price of one in Boisdale - Columnists |newspaper=[[Cape Breton Post]] |date=2015-10-16 |accessdate=2016-02-12}}</ref>, Norah Rendell, Cillian O'Dalaigh, Fiona Black, Ailie Robertson, Ivonne Hernandez }} '''The Outside Track''' is a [[Celtic Music|Pan Celtic]] group that performs Scots, [[Music of Ireland|Irish]] and [[Cape Breton fiddling|Cape Breton]] songs and [[Irish stepdance|stepdance]]. Members of the group include Ailie Robertson who has won a LiveIreland Music Award and was a [[BBC Radio Scotland]] Young Traditional Musician Finalist, and Fiona Black who was a winner of the BBC’s [[Fame Academy]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.shetlandtimes.co.uk/2016/01/14/festival-visiting-acts-range-from-siberia-to-canada |title=Festival visiting acts range from Siberia to Canada &#124; The Shetland Times Ltd |website=Shetlandtimes.co.uk |date=2016-01-14 |accessdate=2016-02-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.mlive.com/entertainment/kalamazoo/index.ssf/2012/04/celtic_band_the_outside_track.html |title=Celtic band The Outside Track comes from different places, different grooves |website=MLive.com |date=2012-04-10 |accessdate=2016-02-12}}</ref>, as well as Mairi Rankin, a member of the [[The Rankin Family|Rankin family]].<ref>{{cite web |title=The Band |url=https://www.theoutsidetrack.com/the-band/ |website=The Outside Track |accessdate=8 October 2018}}</ref> As a group they won ‘Best Group’ in the 2012 LiveIreland Music Award,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tracscotland.org/tracs/traditional-arts-events/2422/the-outside-track |title=The Outside Track &#124; Traditional Arts and Culture Scotland |website=Tracscotland.org |date= |accessdate=2016-02-12}}</ref> a ‘Tradition In Review’ award, and was nominated for the 2013 [[Scots Trad Music Awards|MG Alba Scots Traditional Music Award]]. For their album ''Flash Company'', they also won the German Radio Critics' Prize.<ref>{{cite web|author=David Kidman |url=http://www.folkradio.co.uk/2015/09/the-outside-track-light-up-the-dark/ |title=The Outside Track – Light Up the Dark &#124; Folk Radio UK |website=Folkradio.co.uk |date=2015-09-07 |accessdate=2016-02-12}}</ref>
